The practically-oriented course gives students necessary knowledge and skills for teaching English at primary level. The topics include: teaching vocabulary and language skills, planning and analysing English lessons, using language games, etc.Objectives/eesmärkid:  To provide students with didactic skills for teaching English on the first two school stages.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  On completion of the course the student: - knows and uses the terminology of ELT methodology as well as the theoretical principles related to the topics discussed; - knows the subject field of foreign languages of the National curriculum for basic school (two first school stages) and has an overview of the necessary teaching materials for the two first school stages; - plans English lessons and creates worksheets for primary school students and analyses their own as well as fellow-students' lesson plans and worksheets; - has acquired the most important classroom expressions; - knows and can use methodological techniques for teaching vocabulary and language skills in primary school English lessons.
